    "html": "<html lang=\"en\"><head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Now | Ashioya Jotham Victor</title>\n    <link rel=\"icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"elephant.ico\">\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0/css/all.min.css\">\n    <script src=\"main.js\"></script>\n    <style>\n        * {\n            margin: 0;\n            padding: 0;\n            box-sizing: border-box;\n        }\n\n        body {\n            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, sans-serif;\n            line-height: 1.7;\n            color: #1a1a1a;\n            max-width: 680px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 2rem 1.5rem;\n        }\n\n        nav {\n            margin-bottom: 3rem;\n        }\n\n        nav a {\n            color: #666;\n            text-decoration: none;\n            margin-right: 1.5rem;\n            font-size: 0.95rem;\n        }\n\n        nav a:hover {\n            color: #1a1a1a;\n        }\n\n        h1 {\n            font-size: 2rem;\n            font-weight: 600;\n            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;\n        }\n\n        .updated {\n            font-size: 0.9rem;\n            color: #888;\n            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;\n        }\n\n        .now-section {\n            margin-bottom: 2.5rem;\n        }\n\n        h2 {\n            font-size: 1.1rem;\n            font-weight: 600;\n            color: #444;\n            text-transform: uppercase;\n            letter-spacing: 0.05em;\n            margin-bottom: 0.75rem;\n        }\n\n        p {\n            margin-bottom: 1rem;\n            color: #333;\n        }\n\n        a {\n            color: #0066cc;\n            text-decoration: none;\n        }\n\n        a:hover {\n            text-decoration: underline;\n        }\n\n        .what-is-now {\n            margin-top: 4rem;\n            padding-top: 1.5rem;\n            border-top: 1px solid #eee;\n            font-size: 0.9rem;\n            color: #666;\n        }\n\n        footer {\n            margin-top: 4rem;\n            padding-top: 1.5rem;\n            border-top: 1px solid #eee;\n            font-size: 0.85rem;\n            color: #888;\n        }\n\n        /* Theme toggle */\n        .theme-toggle {\n            background: none;\n            border: none;\n            cursor: pointer;\n            font-size: 1rem;\n            color: #666;\n            padding: 0.25rem;\n            vertical-align: middle;\n        }\n\n        /* Dark mode */\n        body.dark-mode {\n            background: #1a1a2e;\n            color: #e0e0e0;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode nav a {\n            color: #aaa;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode nav a:hover {\n            color: #fff;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode .theme-toggle {\n            color: #aaa;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode h1 {\n            color: #f0f0f0;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode h2 {\n            color: #aaa;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode p {\n            color: #bbb;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode a {\n            color: #6db3f2;\n        }\n\n        body.dark-mode footer {\n            border-top-color: #444;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n\n<body>\n    <nav>\n        <a href=\"index.html\">Home</a>\n        <a href=\"research.html\">Research</a>\n        <a href=\"projects.html\">Projects</a>\n        <a href=\"essays.html\">Essays</a>\n        <a href=\"now.html\">Now</a>\n        <button class=\"theme-toggle\" onclick=\"toggleDarkMode()\">\n            <i class=\"fas fa-moon\"></i>\n        </button>\n    </nav>\n\n    <h1>Now</h1>\n    <p class=\"updated\">Last updated: May 2026</p>\n\n    <div class=\"now-section\">\n        <h2>Working on</h2>\n        <p>Researcher in <a href=\"https://www.amnestykenya.org/\">Amnesty International Kenya</a>'s\n            <a href=\"https://www.amnestykenya.org/rightup-2-0/\">RightUp 2.0</a> program — a youth-led research\n            initiative investigating tech-facilitated repression and how surveillance tools and digital tactics are\n            used to silence activists and civil society.</p>\n        <p>Junior Research Fellow at the <a href=\"https://ilinaprogram.org/\">ILINA Program</a>, focusing on\n            technical AI safety and mechanistic interpretability. I'm building \"runtime safety governors\" using\n            activation steering to detect and correct deceptive model behavior in real-time, specifically testing if\n            these internal safety controls generalize to Swahili.</p>\n        <p>Also leading partnerships at <a href=\"https://gdg.community.dev/gdg-pwani/\">GDG Pwani</a>, now gearing up\n            for <a href=\"https://gdg.community.dev/gdg-pwani/\">IO Extended 2026 Pwani</a>.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"now-section\">\n        <h2>Thinking about</h2>\n        <p>The politics of AI governance. Who gets to decide what \"safe\" means, and whether the current landscape is\n            trending toward pluralism or priesthood. (I wrote about this <a href=\"essays/ai-priesthood.html\">recently</a>.)</p>\n        <p>Also: the gap between alignment research and deployment reality. The field has a theory-practice problem that\n            nobody wants to name directly.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"now-section\">\n        <h2>Reading</h2>\n        <p>Currently reading <a href=\"https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/710964/the-infinity-machine-by-sebastian-mallaby/\"><em>The Infinity Machine</em></a>\n            by Sebastian Mallaby — the biography of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Demis_Hassabis\">Demis Hassabis</a>\n            and the story of <a href=\"https://deepmind.google/\">DeepMind</a>'s quest toward superintelligence.\n            Fascinated by how the arc from chess prodigy to Nobel laureate maps onto questions I think about daily\n            around AI safety and governance.</p>\n        <p>Also re-reading Seeing Like a State (Scott) — keeps being relevant. And working through the Anthropic\n            interpretability papers to trace how the field's assumptions evolved.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <div class=\"now-section\">\n        <h2>Building</h2>\n        <p>A small tool for visualizing attention patterns in a way that's actually useful for debugging. Early stages.\n            May never ship.</p>\n    </div>\n\n    <footer>\n        © Ashioya Jotham Victor\n    </footer>\n\n\n</body></html>",
